FBIS4-47785 "drafr086_e_94002" FBIS-AFR-94-086 Daily Report 3 May 1994 WEST AFRICA Liberia ECOMOG, UNOMIL Blamed for Slow Pace of Peace Process ECOMOG, UNOMIL Blamed for Slow Pace of Peace Process AB0305222694 Gbarnga Radio ELRL in English 1400 GMT 3 May 94 AB0305222694 Gbarnga Radio ELRL English BFN [Text] Citizens in the rest of the country say ECOMOG [Economic Community of West African States Cease-Fire Monitoring Group] and United Nations Observer Mission in Liberia [UNOMIL] are responsible for the slow pace in the Liberian peace process. In a survey conducted by LCN [Liberia Communications Network] News in Gbarnga, the citizens said, although fighting is taking place between the so-called Liberian Peace Council and the NPFL [National Patriotic Front of Liberia] in the southeast of the country, ECOMOG and UNOMIL have not moved in to stop the fighting.
